  "prompt": "How can I retrieve saved messages in Snapchat that got deleted when person unfriended me?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, if someone unfriends you on Snapchat, you typically lose access to the messages exchanged in that chat, including any saved messages. When a conversation is deleted, the messages are no longer accessible from your account, as Snapchat does not retain deleted messages once the friend has removed you.\n\nHere are a few things you can consider:\n\n1. **Check Saved Messages**: If you had previously saved messages in the chat (by tapping and holding on the message), those should remain in the chat history unless the person unfriends you.\n\n2. **Snapshots**: If you have taken screenshots of conversations or messages, you can refer to those saved images on your device.\n\n3. **Chat Backup**: If you have backed up your Snapchat data through Snapchat\u2019s Memories feature or through your device's overall backups, you might be able to recover some of those messages. However, this is not a guaranteed method.\n\n4. **Reaching out**: If appropriate, you could reach out to the person directly and ask if they still have the messages you are looking for.\n\nIn general, privacy and data retention policies for platforms like Snapchat mean that deleted messages are not recoverable once the friend relationship is severed. Always be cautious and mindful when sharing information on social media platforms.",
